API docs by Redocly

Wsf Schedule API (1.0.0)

Download OpenAPI specification:

Wsf Schedule API - Washington State Department of Transportation APIs

active-seasons

Active schedule seasons for WSF routes.

List all active schedule seasons with dates and PDF URLs.

Responses

Production server

https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/schedule/rest/activeseasons

Request samples

  • JavaScript
import { fetchActiveSeasons } from 'ws-dottie/wsf-schedule/core';

const data = await fetchActiveSeasons({
  fetchMode: 'native',
  validate: true
});

console.log(data);

Response samples

  • 200
Content type
application/json

Example of a successful response from the API (showing first item of 2 total)

[
  • {
    • "ScheduleID": 193,
    • "ScheduleName": "Fall 2025",
    • "ScheduleSeason": 2,
    • "SchedulePDFUrl": "http://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/pdf/2025Fall.pdf",
    • "ScheduleStart": "2025-09-21T07:00:00.000Z",
    • "ScheduleEnd": "2025-12-27T08:00:00.000Z"
    }
]

Get sailing schedule for a specific route and trip date.

path Parameters
TripDate
required
string (FetchScheduleByTripDateAndRouteIdInputTripDateParam)

Trip date in YYYY-MM-DD format. Must be within valid date range.

RouteID
required
number (FetchScheduleByTripDateAndRouteIdInputRouteIDParam)

Numeric ID of the route.

Responses

Production server

https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/schedule/rest/schedule/{TripDate}/{RouteID}

Request samples

  • JavaScript
import { fetchScheduleByTripDateAndRouteId } from 'ws-dottie/wsf-schedule/core';

const data = await fetchScheduleByTripDateAndRouteId({
  params: {
    "TripDate": "2025-11-17",
    "RouteID": 9
  },
  fetchMode: 'native',
  validate: true
});

console.log(data);

Get sailing schedule for a terminal pair and trip date.

path Parameters
TripDate
required
string (FetchScheduleByTripDateAndDepartingTerminalIdAndTerminalIdsInputTripDateParam)

Trip date in YYYY-MM-DD format. Must be within valid date range.

DepartingTerminalID
required
number (FetchScheduleByTripDateAndDepartingTerminalIdAndTerminalIdsInputDepartingTerminalIDParam)

Numeric ID of the departing terminal.

ArrivingTerminalID
required
number (FetchScheduleByTripDateAndDepartingTerminalIdAndTerminalIdsInputArrivingTerminalIDParam)

Numeric ID of the arriving terminal.

Responses

Production server

https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/schedule/rest/schedule/{TripDate}/{DepartingTerminalID}/{ArrivingTerminalID}

Request samples

  • JavaScript
import { fetchScheduleByTripDateAndDepartingTerminalIdAndTerminalIds } from 'ws-dottie/wsf-schedule/core';

const data = await fetchScheduleByTripDateAndDepartingTerminalIdAndTerminalIds({
  params: {
    "TripDate": "2025-11-17",
    "DepartingTerminalID": 1,
    "ArrivingTerminalID": 10
  },
  fetchMode: 'native',
  validate: true
});

console.log(data);

Response samples

application/json

List valid arriving terminals for a departing terminal and trip date.

path Parameters
TripDate
required
string (FetchTerminalMatesScheduleInputTripDateParam)

Trip date in YYYY-MM-DD format; must be within valid date range from GetValidDateRange.

TerminalID
required
number (FetchTerminalMatesScheduleInputTerminalIDParam)

Numeric ID of the departing terminal.

Responses

Production server

https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/schedule/rest/terminalmates/{TripDate}/{TerminalID}

Request samples

  • JavaScript
import { fetchTerminalMatesSchedule } from 'ws-dottie/wsf-schedule/core';

const data = await fetchTerminalMatesSchedule({
  params: {
    "TripDate": "2025-11-17",
    "TerminalID": 1
  },
  fetchMode: 'native',
  validate: true
});

console.log(data);

Response samples

  • 200
Content type
application/json

Example of a successful response from the API (showing first item of 4 total)

[
  • {
    • "TerminalID": 10,
    • "Description": "Friday Harbor"
    }
]

List all valid terminal pairs for a trip date.

path Parameters
TripDate
required
string (FetchTerminalsAndMatesInputTripDateParam)

Trip date for which to retrieve all terminal combinations, as a date string in YYYY-MM-DD format. E.g., '2025-11-02' for November 2, 2025. Must be within valid date range from GetScheduleValidDateRange. Used to filter terminal combinations by trip date availability.

Responses

Production server

https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/schedule/rest/terminalsandmates/{TripDate}

Request samples

  • JavaScript
import { fetchTerminalsAndMates } from 'ws-dottie/wsf-schedule/core';

const data = await fetchTerminalsAndMates({
  params: {
    "TripDate": "2025-11-17"
  },
  fetchMode: 'native',
  validate: true
});

console.log(data);

Response samples

  • 200
Content type
application/json

Example of a successful response from the API (showing first item of 38 total)

[
  • {
    • "DepartingTerminalID": 1,
    • "DepartingDescription": "Anacortes",
    • "ArrivingTerminalID": 10,
    • "ArrivingDescription": "Friday Harbor"
    }
]

List valid terminal pairs for a specific route and trip date.

path Parameters
TripDate
required
string (FetchTerminalsAndMatesByRouteInputTripDateParam)

Trip date in YYYY-MM-DD format. Must be within valid date range from GetScheduleValidDateRange.

RouteID
required
number (FetchTerminalsAndMatesByRouteInputRouteIDParam)

Numeric ID of the route.

Responses

Production server

https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/schedule/rest/terminalsandmatesbyroute/{TripDate}/{RouteID}

Request samples

  • JavaScript
import { fetchTerminalsAndMatesByRoute } from 'ws-dottie/wsf-schedule/core';

const data = await fetchTerminalsAndMatesByRoute({
  params: {
    "TripDate": "2025-11-17",
    "RouteID": 9
  },
  fetchMode: 'native',
  validate: true
});

console.log(data);

Response samples

  • 200
Content type
application/json

Example of a successful response from the API (showing first item of 20 total)

[
  • {
    • "DepartingTerminalID": 1,
    • "DepartingDescription": "Anacortes",
    • "ArrivingTerminalID": 10,
    • "ArrivingDescription": "Friday Harbor"
    }
]

sailings

Scheduled ferry sailings organized by route and direction.

List all sailings for scheduled route including inactive sailings.

path Parameters
SchedRouteID
required
number (FetchAllSailingsBySchedRouteIDInputSchedRouteIDParam)

Numeric ID of the scheduled route.

Responses

Production server

https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/schedule/rest/allsailings/{SchedRouteID}

Request samples

  • JavaScript
import { fetchAllSailingsBySchedRouteID } from 'ws-dottie/wsf-schedule/core';

const data = await fetchAllSailingsBySchedRouteID({
  params: {
    "SchedRouteID": 2401
  },
  fetchMode: 'native',
  validate: true
});

console.log(data);

List active sailings for specified scheduled route.

path Parameters
SchedRouteID
required
number (FetchSailingsByRouteIDInputSchedRouteIDParam)

Numeric ID of the scheduled route.

Responses

Production server

https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/schedule/rest/sailings/{SchedRouteID}

Request samples

  • JavaScript
import { fetchSailingsByRouteID } from 'ws-dottie/wsf-schedule/core';

const data = await fetchSailingsByRouteID({
  params: {
    "SchedRouteID": 2401
  },
  fetchMode: 'native',
  validate: true
});

console.log(data);

Response samples

  • 200
Content type
application/json

cache-flush-date-schedule

Cache invalidation timestamp for wsf-schedule static data.

Get timestamp of when static wsf-schedule data was last updated.

Responses

Production server

https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/schedule/rest/cacheflushdate

Request samples

  • JavaScript
import { fetchCacheFlushDateSchedule } from 'ws-dottie/wsf-schedule/core';

const data = await fetchCacheFlushDateSchedule({
  fetchMode: 'native',
  validate: true
});

console.log(data);

Response samples

  • 200
Content type
application/json

Example of a successful response from the API

"2025-11-15T17:40:00.280Z"

route-details

Detailed ferry route information with service details.

List detailed route information for all routes on specified date.

path Parameters
TripDate
required
string (FetchRouteDetailsByTripDateInputTripDateParam)

Trip date in YYYY-MM-DD format. Must be within valid date range from GetScheduleValidDateRange.

Responses

Production server

https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/schedule/rest/routedetails/{TripDate}

Request samples

  • JavaScript
import { fetchRouteDetailsByTripDate } from 'ws-dottie/wsf-schedule/core';

const data = await fetchRouteDetailsByTripDate({
  params: {
    "TripDate": "2025-11-17"
  },
  fetchMode: 'native',
  validate: true
});

console.log(data);

Response samples

  • 200
Content type

Get detailed route information for specific route on date.

path Parameters
TripDate
required
string (FetchRouteDetailsByTripDateAndRouteIdInputTripDateParam)

Trip date in YYYY-MM-DD format. Must be within valid date range from GetScheduleValidDateRange.

Get today's schedule for a terminal pair.

path Parameters
DepartingTerminalID
required
number (FetchScheduleTodayByTerminalsInputDepartingTerminalIDParam)

Numeric ID of the departing terminal.

ArrivingTerminalID
required
number (FetchScheduleTodayByTerminalsInputArrivingTerminalIDParam)

Numeric ID of the arriving terminal.

OnlyRemainingTimes
required
boolean (FetchScheduleTodayByTerminalsInputOnlyRemainingTimesParam)

True to show only remaining departures today; false to include all departures.

Responses

Production server

https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/schedule/rest/scheduletoday/{DepartingTerminalID}/{ArrivingTerminalID}/{OnlyRemainingTimes}

Request samples

  • JavaScript
import { fetchScheduleTodayByTerminals } from 'ws-dottie/wsf-schedule/core';

const data = await fetchScheduleTodayByTerminals({
  params: {
    "DepartingTerminalID": 1,
    "ArrivingTerminalID": 10,
    "OnlyRemainingTimes": false
  },
  fetchMode: 'native',
  validate: true
});

console.log(data);
